<script src="/js/meme-generator.js" defer></script>

<div class="info-section" slot="info">
<h2>Meme Generator - Create Custom Memes Online for Free</h2>
            <p>Our free online Meme Generator lets you create hilarious, shareable memes in seconds. Upload any image, add your top, middle, and bottom text, customize fonts and colors, drop in emoji stickers, and download your finished meme — all without leaving your browser.</p>

            <h3>What Is a Meme Generator?</h3>
            <p>A meme generator is a tool that lets you overlay text and graphics onto images to create internet memes. The classic meme format uses bold white text with a black outline (typically Impact font) placed at the top and bottom of an image, creating a humorous or relatable caption.</p>
            <p>Modern meme culture has evolved far beyond the classic format. Today's memes use a wide variety of fonts, colors, layouts, and image filters. Our generator supports all of these styles, from the timeless Impact-font classic to colorful, minimal, or dark-mode aesthetics.</p>
            <p>Whether you're creating content for social media, making a joke for your group chat, or producing marketing material with a humorous twist, this tool gives you everything you need in one place.</p>

            <h3>Meme Creation Tools</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Upload any image (JPG, PNG, WebP) or drag and drop directly onto the canvas</li>
                <li>Add top, middle, and bottom text with full customization</li>
                <li>Choose from multiple fonts including Impact (classic), Arial Black, Comic Sans, and more</li>
                <li>Adjust font size, text color, stroke color, and stroke width</li>
                <li>Left, center, and right text alignment options</li>
                <li>Optional text shadow with adjustable blur intensity</li>
                <li>Image filters: grayscale, sepia, invert, blur, and brightness</li>
                <li>Emoji sticker panel — click to add, drag to reposition</li>
                <li>One-click text presets: Classic, Dark Mode, Colorful, Minimal</li>
                <li>Download your finished meme as a PNG image</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How to Use the Meme Generator</h3>
            <p>Creating a meme takes less than a minute. Here's how to get started:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Step 1: Click the upload area or drag and drop your image onto the canvas.</li>
                <li>Step 2: Type your top text, middle text (optional), and bottom text in the input fields.</li>
                <li>Step 3: Customize the font, size, color, and stroke using the Text Settings panel.</li>
                <li>Step 4: Optionally apply an image filter or add emoji stickers from the sticker panel.</li>
                <li>Step 5: Click "Download Meme" to save your creation as a PNG file.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Making Memes That Get Shared</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Creating funny memes for sharing on Twitter, Instagram, Reddit, or Discord</li>
                <li>Making reaction images for group chats and messaging apps</li>
                <li>Producing humorous marketing content or social media posts for brands</li>
                <li>Adding captions to screenshots for commentary or satire</li>
                <li>Creating custom memes for inside jokes with friends or colleagues</li>
                <li>Generating educational or explanatory memes for presentations</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Meme Design Tips</h3>
            <p>The best memes are short and punchy. Keep your text to one or two lines per position — the fewer words, the more impact. ALL CAPS is the traditional meme style and tends to read better at a glance, especially on mobile screens where images are small.</p>
            <p>For maximum readability, stick with white text and a black stroke of at least 2–3px. This ensures your text is visible against both light and dark backgrounds. If you're going for a different aesthetic, use the color pickers to find a combination that contrasts well with your image.</p>
            <p>When adding emoji stickers, click to place them at the center of the canvas, then drag them to your desired position. You can adjust the emoji size before adding using the size slider. Use the "Clear All Emojis" button if you want to start fresh with stickers.</p>

            

            <h3>Images Created Locally — Not Uploaded to Any Server</h3>
            <p>Image composition runs locally via Canvas. Your images are never uploaded.</p>
        
            <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What image formats can I use for memes?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>You can upload PNG, JPG, WebP, and GIF images. For animated GIFs, the text is applied to the first frame only. For best results, use high-resolution images so the text remains sharp when shared.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I use custom fonts for meme text?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>The generator includes the classic Impact font (the standard meme font) as well as other options. Impact with white text and black outline is the traditional meme style. You can adjust font size, color, and outline to match your preferred style.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I add text to the top and bottom of a meme?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Use the top text and bottom text fields. The text is automatically positioned at the top and bottom of the image with appropriate padding. You can also drag text elements to reposition them anywhere on the image.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I save memes without the watermark?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>This tool generates memes without any watermark. The downloaded image is clean and ready to share. The image is processed entirely in your browser.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What size should my meme image be?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>For social media sharing, 1200x630px works well for most platforms. Square images (1080x1080px) work best for Instagram. The tool works with any image size, but very small images will have limited space for readable text.</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>

